<br>
And assuming there isn't, wouldn't that make a great spell for druids on Luclin raids?  Seems to me there should be both a single target and group Resist Curse spell (ala the lines of GRM, Seasons, etc.)  While this wouldn't solve druidic needs for the older worlds high end raids, at least it would be great for Ssra and require a druid or two there.  <br>
<br>
<br>
*Mods, feel free to move to Spells forum, but since I tied it into high end raids (Ssra) with druids, thought I'd start the thread here. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uoldoaktree.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Oldoaktree</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 115<br> <font color=#333399>(6/4/02 2:34:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27499.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Curses and why isn't there a Resist Curse spell?</span><hr size=1> I wondered a lot about this.<br>
<br>
One of the developers had posted something somewhere before Luclin had come out about there being TWO new bases of spells, and that priest classes as a result would get more spells than others because they would need to be able to remove the effects and buff the resistances to them.<br>
<br>
I had assumed it would be Light and Dark, like many RPG's use.  But we got just the one (curse).<br>
<br>
I suspect they decided that they wanted the curses to be a big challenge and so never went with the buff effect.<br>
<br>
They may have done something funky in the code too to get the effect in (ie, it may not work like other resists due to the way the programmed).  Are curses even resistable at this point? <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uoldoaktree.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Oldoaktree</A> at: 6/4/02 11:35:46 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/useriena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Seriena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 377<br> <font color=#333399>(6/4/02 3:02:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27499.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Curses and why isn't there a Resist Curse spell?</span><hr size=1> They are resistable. My monk can resist the curse in FG once in a while, for example. 3 casts of Remove Curse doesn't cure it though when it does land. It would definately be nice if we had some sort of Curse resist buff, but the use would be pretty limited. <p><br><br><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=117440" TARGET="_NEW">Seriena,</A> 60 druid<br>
