<A HREF=http://www.soldiers-of-light.net/>Soldiers of Light</A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaidonrufflefuzz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aidon Rufflefuzz</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Hobbit of Love</span><br>  Posts: 757<br> <font color=#333399>(6/4/02 3:27:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27499.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.engtong.com/Valoran/images/60x60/aidon60x60.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Curses and why isn't there a Resist Curse spell?</span><hr size=1> From all that I have seen, curses are resistable by the current resists.  They just aren't curable by them.<br>
<br>
For instance, I'm pretty sure that the Deadly whatever AE curse that the AL uses is resistable by DR.  Its not very resistable, but it is resitable.  I've personally resisted it before.<br>
<br>
It must be removed, however, by Remove Curse or GRC. <p><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=24579">Aidon</a>

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upinepath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pinepath</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 126<br> <font color=#333399>(6/4/02 5:10:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27499.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Curses and why isn't there a Resist Curse spell?</span><hr size=1> Yeah, I doubt they added a new resistance line.  Most likely, they just added a new type of &quot;counter&quot;, basically a flag that can be set to indicate a poison or disease effect now.  So like the player slow spells, that still resist versus magic, but add disease counters, requiring cure disease for removal.  I expect a curse could resist vs fire, cold, disease, etc, the thing that makes it a curse is just that the spell adds curse counters. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utetriancorbec.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tetrian corbec</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 363<br> <font color=#333399>(6/4/02 6:59:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27499.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Curses and why isn't there a Resist Curse spell?</span><hr size=1> They run on normal ressists, just called curse for the cure part. <p><p><B>Tetrian Corbec</B><br>60 Druid 
